{"id": 225049996, "title": "BBC Strictly Come Dancing's Johannes Radebe supported by Annabel Croft as he receives 'honour", "text": "Johannes Radebe has said it is an \"honour\" after he met King Charles at a Princes Trust event. The BBC Strictly Come Dancing pro dancer, who hails from South Africa, shared a snap of himself shaking hands with the monarch on Instagram. \"Had the honor to attend a special reception at Buckingham Palace with the President and Founder of @princestrust, His Majesty The King. We celebrated the award winners and volunteers on everything they've brilliantly achieved,\" Johannes wrote. He said: \"Thanks again to the wonderful team @princestrust.\" The Trust replied: \"Thank you so much for joining us for this year's Prince's Trust Awards! We hope you left as inspired as we were!\" Johannes' former Strictly partner Annabel Croft also replied. \"How special - beautiful pictures,\" she wrote. \"What a wonderful experience for you all! You should be so proud that you\u2019re making a difference to so many people\u2019s lives\u2026 we all love you because you have a good heart,\" a second wrote back. \"Such a totally special day, this is amazing @johannesradebe,\" another posted. \"You are such an inspiration & you should be so proud that you are making a difference to so many people\u2019s lives, what an amazing role model you are,\" they added. \"Sending so much love,\" they said. \"How very special & what a sentational role model u are for these young people @johannesradebe...beautiful photos,\" another commented. Another said: \"Hi Johannes, when I look at this photo it brings tears to my tears, you look so Proud and elegant, you are a credit to your family. \"I hope you get to dance with The Queen it will be amazing. Take care Love and Respect Nicola xxxxxx\" Another wrote: \"I amso happy you are being recognised for your care of people. One minute we are watching you at the Cliffs Pavillion coming out to meet us and then you are spreading your joy at the palace. How wonderful\" In another post, Johannes wrote: \"It's inspiring how the @princestrust helps and encourages young people to not merely exist but thrive...Well done and congratulations to all the winners and mostly to the courageous @i.am.aminaofficial who won the young change maker award. \"The Prince's Trust supports young people who are facing disadvantage and adversity \u2013 including those who have struggled at school, perhaps been in care, are facing long-term unemployment or have been in trouble with the law. The Trust helps to turn their lives around and supports them to move into education, training or employment.\"", "summary": "Strictly Come Dancing pro dancer, who hails from South Africa, shared a snap of himself shaking hands with the monarch on Instagram.", "url": "https://www.birminghammail.co.uk/news/showbiz-tv/bbc-strictly-come-dancings-johannes-29258930", "image": "https://i2-prod.birminghammail.co.uk/news/showbiz-tv/article29258941.ece/ALTERNATES/s1200/0_johannes.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-05-29 14:13:24", "author": "James Rodger", "authors": ["James Rodger"], "language": "en", "source_country": "gb", "sentiment": 0.784}